element.name: Sidetracked - Rush by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)

p.b: The Rush & Lusk railway station is located on the Dublin-Belfast Railway line

long-description.p:
The station opened in 1844 it consists of the main building built by Great Northern Railway it still retains its original booking office doors.
The typical GNR station masters house is boarded up along with the disused signal cabin.
The footbridge at the station was used in The “Micheal Collins” movie.
Side-Tracked Caches are intended to provide quick Cache-and-dashes at Train Stations.
The Cache is a small micro container please rehide it well to prevent the many muggles from discovering it.
